  skos:note "(1) The formal name was adopted in November 2004 as per the letter of 9 November 2004 from the Permanent Mission of Afghanistan to the United Nations.<br>(2) The formal name was previously changed from \"Afghanistan\" to \"Transitional Islamic State of Afghanistan\" per letter from the Permanent Mission 9 March 2004.<br>(3) Between 7 October 2002 and 2 January 2003 a new afghani [monetary unit] was introduced with the ISO code AFN. The first afghani (ISO code: AFA) was introduced in 1925 replacing the rupee. In addition to being subdivided into 100 pul 20 afghani were equal to the amani.<br>(4) Currency in Pashto/Persian: افغانۍ"@en, "Le nom \"République islamique d'Afghanistan\" a remplacé \"État transitoire islamique d'Afghanistan\" le 9 novembre 2004. [La variante initialement retenue à l'ONU (début mars 2004) \"État islamique transitionnel d'Afghanistan\" avait été écartée en avril 2004 pour s'aligner sur l'usage adopté (fin mars 2004) par la Commission de terminologie du Ministère des affaires étrangères (France)]. Variante (langue): pachtou."@fr ;
