<http://metadata.un.org/unterm/97753e65-3597-4af3-accd-ac29446db9d3>
  a skos:Concept, unterm:Country ;
  dct:identifier "97753e65-3597-4af3-accd-ac29446db9d3" ;
  dct:type "country" ;
  dct:created "2015-05-20T11:59:48.9+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  dct:modified "2024-12-09T19:37:44.519+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  dct:creator "desalegn biru/ny/uno" ;
  dct:contributor "georges.sene" ;
  skos:prefLabel "ميانمار"@ar, "缅甸"@zh, "Myanmar"@en, "Myanmar (le)"@fr, "Myanmar"@es, "Мьянма"@ru ;
  skos:altLabel "جمهورية اتحاد ميانمار"@ar, "缅甸联邦共和国"@zh, "the Republic of the Union of Myanmar"@en, "la République de l'Union du Myanmar"@fr, "la República de la Unión de Myanmar"@es, "Республика Союз Мьянма"@ru ;
  skos:definition "<br>"@zh ;
  skos:note "2011年3月30日，正式国名由“缅甸联邦”改为“缅甸联邦共和国”，简称仍为“缅甸”。缅甸分七个省(division or region)、七个邦(state)和一个联邦区(Union Territory)。省是缅族主要聚居区，邦多为各少数民族聚居地，联邦区是首都内比都。"@zh, "- The Protocol and Liaison Service sent a memo dated 6 April 2011 informing of the change of the official name from \"Union of Myanmar\" to \"Republic of the Union of Myanmar\" as of 30 March 2011. The short name remained unchanged.<br>- Former capital Yangon (a.k.a Rangoon) - from 1948 until November 2005.<br>- The administrative capital of Myanmar was officially moved to a site two miles west of Pyinmana on 6 November 2005.<br>- Nay Pyi Taw (also spelt Naypyidaw) is located in Kyatpyae Village of Pyinmana Township of Mandalay Division. Kyatpyae in Burmese means \"flee under struggle\". Nay Pyi Taw means \"Royal Palace/City\" but is also translated as \"seat of kings\"."@en, "Le 30 mars 2011 la version précédente \"l'Union du Myanmar\" a été abandonnée en faveur de la version indiquée en vedette. La version brève n'a cependant pas été modifiée.Précédemment et variante hors ONU: la Birmanie et l'Union de Birmanie. La capitale était précédemment Yangon (autrefois: Rangoun).Forme variante de la capitale: Pyinmana \"demeure des rois\".La capitale a été déplacée à Nay Pyi Taw (près de Pyinmana) en 2005."@fr, "DRAE: birmano"@es, "В ноябре 2005 г. объявлено о переносе столицы из Янгона (до 1989 г. - Рангун) в г. Пьинмана, а в марте 2006 г. столица была перенесена в отдельный укрепрайон этого города — Нейпьидо.<br>Источник: http://www.sms-tass.ru/client"@ru ;
