<http://metadata.un.org/unterm/089a6443-0bba-4dd2-bc8d-a4888bb508b8>
  a skos:Concept, unterm:Country ;
  dct:identifier "089a6443-0bba-4dd2-bc8d-a4888bb508b8" ;
  dct:type "country" ;
  dct:created "2015-05-20T11:58:49.007+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  dct:modified "2025-07-28T19:47:46.045+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  dct:creator "desalegn biru/ny/uno" ;
  dct:contributor "mónica.pérez ruiz" ;
  skos:prefLabel "هولندا (مملكة -)"@ar, "荷兰王国"@zh, "Netherlands (Kingdom of the)"@en, "Pays-Bas (Royaume des)"@fr, "Países Bajos (Reino de los)"@es, "Нидерланды (Королевство)"@ru ;
  skos:altLabel "مملكة هولندا"@ar, "荷兰王国"@zh, "the Kingdom of the Netherlands"@en, "le Royaume des Pays-Bas"@fr, "el Reino de los Países Bajos"@es, "Королевство Нидерландов"@ru ;
  skos:note "1. It is incorrect to refer to the euro by nationality, for example as an Austrian euro or Belgian euro. However, one may refer to a country’s holdings of euro, for example euro (France) or euro (Germany). The guilder was the former currency unit.&nbsp;<div>2. The capital is Amsterdam, even though the States General and the Government have both been&nbsp;situated in The Hague (the seat of government) since 1588. The status of Amsterdam as capital city is governed by the Constitution of 24 August 1815 and its successors.</div>"@en, "Amsterdam est la capitale constitutionnelle. La Haye est le siège du gouvernement du Parlement et des ambassades."@fr, "Con arreglo a la comunicación de fecha 3 de marzo de 2023 dirigida a la Oficina Ejecutiva del Secretario General por la Misión Permanente del Reino de los Países Bajos, el nombre corto del país dejó de ser \"Países Bajos (los)” y pasó a ser “Países Bajos (Reino de los)”."@es ;
