  skos:note "The EC$ (East Caribbean dollar) is the legal tender in the following member countries of the East Caribbean Central Bank (ECCB): Antigua and Barbuda, Dominica, Grenada, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia and Saint Vincent and the Grenadines. One often finds the abbreviated name St. Lucia, including on government websites, but this form is not used at the UN."@en, "DRAE: santalucense"@es, "Восточнокарибский доллар - валюта имеющая хождение в ряде стран входящих в Организацию Восточно-Карибских государств."@ru ;
