  skos:altLabel "جزر كوك"@ar, "库克群岛"@zh, "the Cook Islands"@en, "les Îles Cook"@fr, "las Islas Cook"@es, "Острова Кука"@ru ;
  skos:definition "Member of specialized agencies (status current as of June 2017)."@en ;
  skos:note "N.B.: The Cook Islands is a State in free association with New Zealand but not a United Nations Member State. Maori name: Kūki 'Āirani.<br>- The 15 small islands have a total land area of 240 square kilometres though the Cook Islands Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) covers 1.8 million square kilometres of ocean. Main population centre on the island of Rarotonga.<br>- Cook Islands dollar also used."@en, "État autonome associé à la Nouvelle-Zélande."@fr ;
